Extracted the migration logic (~320 lines) from `agr/commands/sync.py` into a new `agr/commands/migrations.py` module. This improves separation of concerns — the migration functions were already used across `sync`, `add`, and `remove` commands, making them a cross-cutting concern rather than sync-specific logic. The sync module went from 700 lines to 370, and all 584 tests continue to pass.
